The paper proposes an end-to-end deep learning model for time series prediction, which involves spatio-temporal feature extraction and temporal dynamics modeling. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). However, given the focus on deep learning and neural networks, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The use of attention mechanisms and recurrent highway networks also suggests a focus on sequential data, which further supports the likelihood of cs.LG and cs.AI. The other sub-categories are less likely but still possible, as they could be relevant to specific applications or aspects of the proposed model.
